Refers to the probability of default type, either Marginal or Cumulative. It contains the value M or C, corresponding to Marginal PD or Cumulative PD respectively.

attributes.logicalName: Probability of Default Term Structure Code
attributes.gcd: Refers to the PD Term Structure Identifier represents a specific set of PD term structures against multiple homogenous credit identifiers. Each series have a set of probability to default values against multiple time periods. Credit Identifiers could either be Rating or Delinquency Past Due days band. One ID can only be either Rating based or DPD based but not both. Ideally, a PD Term structure Identifier will be associated to a specific PD Term Structure model which used by the banking institution to generate the PD values.

attributes.logicalName: Probability of Default Term Structure Description
attributes.gcd: Refers to the description that describes the features of the PD Term Structure identifier (likely associated to a model).

attributes.logicalName: Probability of Default Term Structure Frequency Unit
attributes.gcd: Refers to the frequency at which the PD values are generated (valid for). The possible values are M - Monthly, Q-Quarterly, H- Half Yearly, Y-Yearly, D- Daily.

attributes.logicalName: Probability of Default Term Structure Name
attributes.gcd: Refers to the PD Term Structure Name which represents the unique features of the PD Term Structure identifier (likely associated to a model).

attributes.logicalName: Probability of Default Term Structure Numeric Identifier
attributes.gcd: Refers to the equivalent numeric identifier of the Probability of Default Term Structure Numeric Identifier.

attributes.logicalName: Probability of Default Term Structure Type
attributes.gcd: Refers to the value that indicates the basis of PD Term Structure, either Rating based or DPD based. It contains the value 'R' or 'D' for Rating or DPD band respectively.
